-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Toroid - Open Source Middleware
Portions Copyright 2008 Brian McManus, Linopoly, LLC GPL V2

Requirements: 
Apache PHP5, PEAR, MySQL, git
	-Debian/Ubuntu e.g. apt-get install apache2 php5 php5-mysql libapache2-mod-php5 php-pear git-core

Optional:
xmltv
	-Debian/Ubuntu: aptitude install xmltv

Install instructions:
Make sure you have pear, and install required PEAR components:
	pear install MDB2 MDB2_Driver_mysql Auth Pager

Create directory for toroid, I've opted to use /opt
 mkdir -p /opt

Downloads files using git, allow Smarty templates cache writing.
 cd /opt
 git clone git://toroid.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/toroid
 chmod a+rwx /opt/toroid/admin/templates_c
 cd toroid 


Create MySQL database, Import default database schema:
 mysqladmin create toroid
 mysql -u root toroid < sql/default.sql

Optional: Import 'tms' schema (if using Tribune Media Systems epg source):
 mysql -u root toroid < sql/tms.sql

Configure Apache to use a Virtual Host for toroid
 An example apache config is in /opt/toroid/contrib/apache2/001-toroid at this point.
 You can do this with a subdomain, or an /etc/hosts entry.
 Or make an aliases directory of /toroid to /opt/toroid/admin
   e.g. Alias /toroid/ "/opt/toroid/admin"

Restart Apache2
 /etc/init.d/apache2 restart

Optional: Configure XMLTV for developer use with schedulesdirect.org
 *Please note that production systems must obtain a license for
 *for Tribune Medias channel line up listing.
   sudo tv_grab_na_dd --configure --config-file /opt/toroid/etc/xmltv.conf
Login, point your browser to your server
 http://toroid.whatever.host/

 default username: admin
 default password: 2ez4u
  (I know, I know, a tad bit insecure, but when we have
   an automated install process we will prompt them for it.)

